thread.title: Sinkhole Mona Vale

author: Robbie Patterson
title: Sinkhole Mona Vale
text:
A hole in the road in Mona Vale which Sydney Water dug after a water main burst. Manly Sydney Water’s bid to fix burst water main creates large hole at a Mona Vale corner Robbie Patterson, 22, 2017 9:07am Is this Sydney’s oldest dog? ‘You’d think I’d be sick of meat but I love it’
A LARGE crater has opened up in a suburban street on Sydney’s northern beaches after roadworks to repair a burst water main stalled.
The hole, which a resident described as a “sinkhole” has spread across two lanes at the corner of Park and Maxwell streets, about 1km away from the Mona Vale town centre.
Sydney Water was doing works to repair a burst water main which occurred about 2am.
A spokesman said the water was shut off at 3am, and they began digging but the digging stalled when the Sydney Water found a storm water pipe and gas main.
“We need help from the (Northern Beaches) council which owns the storm water pipe and another company (AGL) before we repair the water main,” the spokesman said.
“The ground has not subsided or collapsed at all, it is not a sinkhole. It could look bigger than it is because there is a stormwater pipe below it.”
Park St has been closed by Sydney Water and traffic diversions have been put in place.
VAST SINKHOLE CAUSES MAJOR BRIDGE COLLAPSE IN VLADIVOSTOK Russia: Vast sinkhole causes major bridge collapse in Vladivostok 1:05 A vast sinkhole caused a major road bridge to collapse in Vladivostok, Tuesday. The hole is approximately 20 metres (65.6ft) deep, while the structural damage inflicted to its surroundings spans 10 x 10 metres (32.8ft x 32.8ft). Police and emergency services have already blocked off Stanykovicha Street and the construction site where the sinkhole occurred, and evacuated local residents as well as employees and students of Primorsky Territory Institute of Education Development from the area. No casualties have been reported. The Governor of Primorsky Territory Vladimir Miklushevshky has called for local transport officers to conduct an investigation.

It’s unknown at this stage when the road will be fixed.
